#: ../../D/Death--X-of.rst:5
msgid "Death, X of"
msgstr "Death, X of"

#: ../../D/Death--X-of.rst:7
msgid ""
"[common] A construction used to imbue the subject with campy menace, usually"
" with intent to ridicule. The ancestor of this term is a famous *Far Side* "
"cartoon from the 1980s in which a balloon with a fierce face painted on it "
"is passed off as the \"Floating Head of Death\". Hackers and SF fans have "
"been using the suffix \"of Death\" ever since to label things which appear "
"to be vastly threatening but will actually pop like a balloon if you prick "
"them. Such constructions are properly spoken in a tone of over-exagerrated "
"portentiousness: \"Behold! The Spinning - Pizza - of - Death!\" See "
":ref:`Blue-Screen-of-Death`\\, :ref:`Ping-O--Death`\\, :ref:`Spinning-Pizza-"
"of-Death`\\, :ref:`click-of-death`\\. Compare :ref:`Doom--X-of`\\."
msgstr ""
"[一般的] 通常は嘲笑の意図をもって、対象に芝居がかった脅威を吹き込むために使われる言い回し。この用語の元祖は、1980年代の有名な『*Far "
"Side*』の漫画で、獰猛な顔が描かれた風船が「Floating Head of "
"Death(死の浮遊する頭)」として通用しているものである。それ以来、ハッカーやSFファンは、途方もなく脅威的に見えるが、突けば風船のようにはじけてしまうものを表すのに、接尾辞「of"
" Death」を使ってきた。こうした言い回しは、大げさに芝居がかった重々しさの口調で口にするのが正しい。「Behold! The Spinning - "
"Pizza - of - Death!」のように。\\ :ref:`Blue-Screen-of-Death`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Ping-O--"
"Death`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Spinning-Pizza-of-Death`\\ 、\\ :ref:`click-of-death`\\ "
"を参照。\\ :ref:`Doom--X-of`\\ と比較せよ。"
